text: The Tseax River Cone (also known as Aiyansh Volcano) is a cinder cone in British Columbia, Canada. The volcano and the area around it are protected as a provincial park called the Nisga'a Memorial Lava Beds Provincial Park. In the 18th century it caused the death of about 2000 people. == References == Category:Volcanoes of British Columbia
